Disable KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE to fix vmlinux link with Bootlin toolchain.

The Bootlin aarch64-glibc-stable toolchain places the kernel at virtual
address 0xffffff8008080000. KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE stores symbol offsets
as 32-bit values relative to the lowest symbol address; the gap between
the kernel link base and this address exceeds 2^31, causing the
"relative symbol value out of range in relative mode" error during
vmlinux assembly.

Changing the default to n causes kallsyms to fall back to absolute 64-bit
addresses, which always work at the cost of slightly larger kallsyms table.
KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE is a promptless bool and cannot be overridden by
config fragments.

--- a/init/Kconfig
+++ b/init/Kconfig
@@ -1347,7 +1347,7 @@ config KALLSYMS_BASE_RELATIVE
 	bool
 	depends on KALLSYMS
-	default !IA64 && !(TILE && 64BIT)
+	default n
 	help
 	  Instead of emitting them as absolute values in the native word size,
